language-name:
{{doc-important|Don't write "English" in your language!}}

'''Write the name of ''your'' language in its native script.'''

If a Wikimedia project in your language (such as your language’s Wikipedia) is written in more than one script, include all the scripts, separated by <code>&nbsp;/&nbsp;</code>. For example, include all the scripts if MediaWiki automatically transliterates between them, or if there are many articles in each script, or if the main page features both scripts prominently.

'''Important:''' Do not use your language’s word for “English”. Use the word that your language uses to refer to itself. If you translate this message to mean “English” in your language, your change will be reverted.
